<h1>ReMatch</h1>

<p>
ReMatch is a web-based tool for integration of user-given
stoichiometric metabolic models into a database collected from public
data sources such as 
<a href="http://www.genome.jp/kegg/">KEGG</a>, 
<a href="http://metacyc.org/">MetaCyc</a>, 
<a href="http://www.ebi.ac.uk/chebi/">CheBI</a> and 
<a href="http://www.metabolome.jp/">ARM</a>.
ReMatch is geared particularly towards 13C metabolic flux analysis: 
it is possible to augment the model with carbon mappings and export
the model to analysis in 13C flux analysis software.

<p>
The service is free for academic institutions.
</p>

<p>
<a href="http://sysdb.cs.helsinki.fi/ReMatch" onClick="javascript: pageTracker._trackPageview('/services/rematch-login');">ReMatch login</a>
</p>

<h2>Status</h2>

<p>
